ovember 2024**\n  - The company officially rebranded from Codeium to Windsurf in **April 2025**\n  - Andrej Karpathy defined \"vibe coding\" (a key Windsurf concept) in **February 2025**\n\n### Competition with Cursor:\n- **Direct Competitor**: Windsurf is positioned as a direct competitor to Cursor in the AI programming assistant market\n- **Market Position**: While Cursor was the dominant AI coding tool in 2024 (\"crowning year\"), Windsurf emerged as a challenger in 2025\n- **Key Differentiator**: Windsurf's \"Flow\" architecture for handling large-scale enterprise codebases\n\n### Recent Developments:\n- **Acquisition**: In **May 2025**, OpenAI acquired Windsurf for **$3 billion**\n- **Growth Metrics**: By April 2025, Windsurf had:\n  - Over 1 million developers using the platform\n  - Around $100 million in ARR (annual recurring revenue)\n  - More than 1,000 enterprise customers\n\n### Product Features:\n- Based on a VSCode fork (similar to Cursor)\n- Supports over 70 programming languages\n- Known for better cost control and private deployment capabilities compared to Cursor\n- Features \"Cascade\" - an early AI IDE agent\n\n**Note**: The search results don't explicitly mention a \"February 2025 launch\" for a new Windsurf competitor. The closest match is the February 2025 timeframe when Andrej Karpathy defined \"vibe coding\" concepts related to Windsurf and similar platforms.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
