 **Votes:** 789\n- **Description:** A browser-based tool powered by Claude Code that transforms your browser into a local computer. It's designed for everyone from creators to builders, enabling real work from programming to design to daily tasks without setup or learning curves.\n- **Date:** February 11, 2026\n\n### 2. **The new v0 by Vercel**\n- **Tagline:** \"Full-stack vibe coding platform\"\n- **Votes:** 368\n- **Description:** A collaborative AI assistant that helps you design, iterate, and scale full-stack web applications. Created by Vercel as a comprehensive coding platform.\n- **Date:** February 5, 2026\n\n### 3. **Oz by Warp**\n- **Tagline:** \"Run hundreds of cloud agents simultaneously\"\n- **Votes:** 176\n- **Description:** An orchestration platform for cloud agents that lets you launch hundreds of cloud agents from Warp, CLI tools, or even your phone. Wake up to production-ready pull requests.\n- **Date:** February 11, 2026\n\n### 4. **Willow for Developers**\n- **Tagline:** \"Voice input for Cursor and AI IDEs\"\n- **Votes:** 147\n- **Description:** Voice input experience optimized for developers. Communicate directly with AI IDEs like Cursor and Antigravity via voice with 3x the accuracy of built-in options. Includes technical term recognition (SQL, API, REST, etc.).\n- **Date:** February 11, 2026\n\n### 5. **GitHub Agent HQ**\n- **Tagline:** \"Use Claude, Codex, and Copilot directly in GitHub and VS Code\"\n- **Votes:** 178\n- **Description:** Anthropic's Claude and OpenAI Codex now available in public preview within GitHub and VS Code (requires Copilot Pro+ or Copilot Enterprise subscription).\n- **Date:** February 5, 2026\n\n---\n\n## **Other Notable AI Programming Tools from February 2026:**\n\n- **Miro MCP** - Converts code to visual documentation and whiteboard content to code (125 votes)\n- **Inspector** - Visual editor that connects with AI assistants like Claude Code and Cursor for automatic code updates\n\n---\n\nWould you like more detail