e entry point for all three AI agents\n- Previously these tools worked separately, but now they're integrated into one workspace\n\n### 💻 **Platform Support**\n- **GitHub web interface**\n- **GitHub Mobile app**\n- **VS Code** (version 1.109+ with deep native integration)\n\n### 💰 **Pricing**\n- **$39/month** subscription\n- Available to Copilot Pro Plus and Enterprise subscribers\n- Each AI agent call counts as a premium request (subject to subscription quotas)\n\n### 🚀 **Core Capabilities**\n1. **Task Assignment**: Assign the same issue to multiple AI agents simultaneously\n2. **Context Switching**: Seamless switching between different AI assistants\n3. **Multi-Agent Workflows**: Different AI agents can handle different aspects of development:\n   - Claude: Known for logical reasoning and transparent \"chain of thought\"\n   - Codex: Strong in code generation and logic\n   - Copilot: Overall coordination and completion\n\n### 📱 **Development Workflow Integration**\n- Works in issues, pull requests, and code review processes\n- Developers can @mention specific AI agents (e.g., @Claude, @Codex)\n- Supports comparing code generation quality across different AIs\n\n## Strategic Significance\n\nThis launch represents what many are calling the **\"Fleet Commander Era\"** of programming - where developers become coordinators of AI agent teams rather than individual coders. GitHub is positioning itself as a neutral platform (\"the Switzerland of AI programming\") that hosts multiple AI providers rather than competing directly with them.\n\nThe integration aims to solve the **context switching problem** that developers face when moving between different AI tools, creating a seamless workflow within the existing GitHub ecosystem.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
      }
