1. Kilo Code Reviewer (Kilocode)**\n- **Launch**: Late January 2026 (Jan 27) - still prominent in February\n- **Description**: Automated AI code review tool for engineering teams\n- **Features**: \n  - Automatic AI review of every pull request\n  - Supports 500+ models (Claude, GPT, Gemini, and free options)\n  - Provides structured feedback on performance, security, style, and test coverage\n- **Upvotes**: 614 votes\n\n**2. Inspector - \"Figma for Claude Code\"**\n- **Launch**: February 5, 2026\n- **Description**: Visual editing tool that connects with AI assistants like Claude Code, Codex, and Cursor\n- **Features**: \n  - Lets designers edit production website frontends visually\n  - Automatically writes changes to codebase\n  - Eliminates design handoff process\n- **Upvotes**: 462 votes (Featured)\n- **Achievement**: Daily and weekly winner (Feb 5)\n\n**3. Straion**\n- **Launch**: February 22-23, 2026\n- **Description**: AI coding agent with enterprise-level code automation\n- **Features**:\n  - Centralized rule management\n  - Integration with Claude Code, GitHub Copilot, Cursor\n  - Automated coding for efficiency\n- **Upvotes**: 349 votes\n\n**4. Base44 Backend Platform**\n- **Launch**: February 17, 2026\n- **Description**: Backend platform for the AI era\n- **Features**:\n  - Complete backend service for AI agent applications\n  - Full-stack application deployment\n  - No configuration required\n  - Optimized for Claude Code and Cursor\n- **Upvotes**: 462 votes\n\n**5. JDoodle.ai**\n- **Launch**: February 17, 2026\n- **Description**: Website development through chat generation\n- **Features**:\n  - Frontend and backend development\n  - Full-stack application creation\n  - Integration with ChatGPT and Claude\n  - Real-time preview\n  - Publish links\n- **Upvotes**: 192 votes\n\n**6. Various Claude Code-integrated Tools**:\n- **Open blivz** (Feb 18-19): Open source tool for customizing tech stack with Claude Code\n- **Axel** (Feb 9): AI programming assistant with task management\n- **1Code** (Jan 17): Cursor-like UI with Claude Code integration\n\n### **Notable Trends:**\n- **Claude Code integration** was a major theme across multiple products\n- **AI code review** tools gained significant traction\n- **Visual-to-code** tools (like Inspector) bridged design and development\n- **Full-stack AI development platforms** emerged as a category\n\n---\n\n**Note**: The search results didn't provide exact daily breakdowns for February 14-28, 2026, but these products were active and featured during that February 2026 period. For more detailed daily launch information, you would need to access Product Hunt's archives directly or use their API with specific date parameters.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
